item.title: Error cant find out what it is
item.dc:creator: @Skiire Skiire
item.description:
@Skiire wrote:

I’ve heard a lot about issues regarding InsidiaX. My only alternative would be to completely delete the cache you downloaded from the thread and start from scratch, if it still doesn’t work, I don’t think it’s downloading properly. To fix it search for a link that it’s downloading from (I haven’t a clue what class as I’ve never opened an InsidiaX) and change it to a working one. You can probably find a re-upload on the thread itself somewhere. That’s about all the advice I can give you. Good luck!

item.title: Error cant find out what it is
item.dc:creator: @Skiire Skiire
item.description:
@Skiire wrote:

It’s telling you it’s missing the file “mapConfig.txt”

Open the cache and rename the file in the maps folder to mapConfig.txt. It’s maplocation when you download it.
